race.comment: GOLDEN AGE (5) doesn't boast the best winning strike rate but ran a nice race last time out, finishing third and beaten only 1.2 lengths over 1200m at Moe. That was a much tougher race than this, so looks well-placed. SHANGHAI VENTURE (8) finished 0.9 lengths from the winner in fourth last start after being prominent at the turn over 1115m at Kyneton, an improvement on her sixth at Geelong the run before. KENTAHTEN (1) was only narrowly beaten last time out, which followed a suitable first-up run and has previously demonstrated a liking for this track. DOMINANT MISS (11) has not won for a long while. Last raced on November 18 when beaten 2 lengths into sixth at Kyneton over 1115m. Placed to advantage so expect a better run this time. ELLMAKNIFICO (14) progressed nicely last start to finish a close second over 1200m at Bairnsdale after missing the placings at the previous appearance and looks to have found a suitable race.
